==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tulip-shell
<hw>Tu"lip-shell`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A large, handsomely colored, marine univalve shell
(<spn>Fasciolaria tulipa</spn>) native of the Southern United States.
The name is sometimes applied also to other species of
<gen>Fasciolaria</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tulipwood</ent>⟦br⟧
